The paper deals with a data structure for point sets, which is a common topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The focus on compression and efficient queries suggests that it could also fit in the data structures (cs.DS) and database management (cs.DM) categories. The use of clustering and experimental evidence suggests that it could also be relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and computer vision (cs.CV).
